{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":999,"text":"Over a million people are killed\neach year in disasters."},{"time":5999,"text":"Two and a half million people\nwill be permanently disabled or displaced,"},{"time":11257,"text":"and the communities will take\n20 to 30 years to recover"},{"time":15205,"text":"and billions of economic losses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19054,"text":"If you can reduce\nthe initial response by one day,"},{"time":23449,"text":"you can reduce the overall recovery"},{"time":27000,"text":"by a thousand days, or three years."},{"time":29832,"text":"See how that works?"},{"time":31609,"text":"If the initial responders\ncan get in, save lives,"},{"time":34483,"text":"mitigate whatever flooding\ndanger there is,"},{"time":37023,"text":"that means the other groups can get in"},{"time":39331,"text":"to restore the water,\nthe roads, the electricity,"},{"time":42340,"text":"which means then the construction people,\nthe insurance agents,"},{"time":45480,"text":"all of them can get in\nto rebuild the houses,"},{"time":48118,"text":"which then means\nyou can restore the economy,"},{"time":51130,"text":"and maybe even make it better\nand more resilient to the next disaster."},{"time":57899,"text":"A major insurance company told me"},{"time":59719,"text":"that if they can get a homeowner's claim\nprocessed one day earlier,"},{"time":64855,"text":"it'll make a difference of six months"},{"time":66999,"text":"in that person getting\ntheir home repaired."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70118,"text":"And that's why I do disaster robotics --"},{"time":72471,"text":"because robots can\nmake a disaster go away faster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78305,"text":"Now, you've already seen\na couple of these."},{"time":80346,"text":"These are the UAVs."},{"time":82090,"text":"These are two types of UAVs:"},{"time":83975,"text":"a rotorcraft, or hummingbird;"},{"time":85864,"text":"a fixed-wing, a hawk."},{"time":87958,"text":"And they're used extensively since 2005 --"},{"time":91372,"text":"Hurricane Katrina."},{"time":92571,"text":"Let me show you how this hummingbird,\nthis rotorcraft, works."},{"time":95919,"text":"Fantastic for structural engineers."},{"time":98999,"text":"Being able to see damage from angles you\ncan't get from binoculars on the ground"},{"time":103443,"text":"or from a satellite image,"},{"time":104777,"text":"or anything flying at a higher angle."},{"time":108530,"text":"But it's not just structural engineers\nand insurance people who need this."},{"time":112926,"text":"You've got things\nlike this fixed-wing, this hawk."},{"time":115417,"text":"Now, this hawk can be used\nfor geospatial surveys."},{"time":118712,"text":"That's where you're\npulling imagery together"},{"time":121585,"text":"and getting 3D reconstruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123434,"text":"We used both of these at the Oso mudslides\nup in Washington State,"},{"time":127532,"text":"because the big problem"},{"time":129755,"text":"was geospatial and hydrological\nunderstanding of the disaster --"},{"time":132937,"text":"not the search and rescue."},{"time":134207,"text":"The search and rescue teams\nhad it under control"},{"time":136550,"text":"and knew what they were doing."},{"time":138052,"text":"The bigger problem was that river\nand mudslide might wipe them out"},{"time":141946,"text":"and flood the responders."},{"time":143464,"text":"And not only was it challenging\nto the responders and property damage,"},{"time":147230,"text":"it's also putting at risk\nthe future of salmon fishing"},{"time":150533,"text":"along that part of Washington State."},{"time":152273,"text":"So they needed to understand\nwhat was going on."},{"time":154773,"text":"In seven hours, going from Arlington,"},{"time":157406,"text":"driving from the Incident Command Post\nto the site, flying the UAVs,"},{"time":162244,"text":"processing the data, driving back\nto Arlington command post --"},{"time":165999,"text":"seven hours."},{"time":167429,"text":"We gave them in seven hours\ndata that they could take"},{"time":170987,"text":"only two to three days\nto get any other way --"},{"time":174761,"text":"and at higher resolution."},{"time":177064,"text":"It's a game changer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179773,"text":"And don't just think about the UAVs."},{"time":181866,"text":"I mean, they are sexy -- but remember,"},{"time":184518,"text":"80 percent of the world's\npopulation lives by water,"},{"time":187878,"text":"and that means our critical\ninfrastructure is underwater --"},{"time":190766,"text":"the parts that we can't get to,\nlike the bridges and things like that."},{"time":194076,"text":"And that's why we have\nunmanned marine vehicles,"},{"time":196692,"text":"one type of which you've already met,\nwhich is SARbot, a square dolphin."},{"time":201168,"text":"It goes underwater and uses sonar."},{"time":203888,"text":"Well, why are marine vehicles so important"},{"time":206245,"text":"and why are they very, very important?"},{"time":209393,"text":"They get overlooked."},{"time":210933,"text":"Think about the Japanese tsunami --"},{"time":213359,"text":"400 miles of coastland totally devastated,"},{"time":217349,"text":"twice the amount of coastland devastated\nby Hurricane Katrina in the United States."},{"time":222069,"text":"You're talking about your bridges,\nyour pipelines, your ports -- wiped out."},{"time":225949,"text":"And if you don't have a port,"},{"time":227585,"text":"you don't have a way\nto get in enough relief supplies"},{"time":230855,"text":"to support a population."},{"time":232100,"text":"That was a huge problem\nat the Haiti earthquake."},{"time":235565,"text":"So we need marine vehicles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237711,"text":"Now, let's look at a viewpoint\nfrom the SARbot"},{"time":240166,"text":"of what they were seeing."},{"time":241661,"text":"We were working on a fishing port."},{"time":243931,"text":"We were able to reopen that fishing port,\nusing her sonar, in four hours."},{"time":249671,"text":"That fishing port was told\nit was going to be six months"},{"time":252348,"text":"before they could get\na manual team of divers in,"},{"time":255078,"text":"and it was going to take\nthe divers two weeks."},{"time":257789,"text":"They were going to miss\nthe fall fishing season,"},{"time":260107,"text":"which was the major economy for that part,\nwhich is kind of like their Cape Cod."},{"time":264357,"text":"UMVs, very important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266649,"text":"But you know, all the robots\nI've shown you have been small,"},{"time":269921,"text":"and that's because robots\ndon't do things that people do."},{"time":273722,"text":"They go places people can't go."},{"time":275999,"text":"And a great example of that is Bujold."},{"time":278999,"text":"Unmanned ground vehicles\nare particularly small,"},{"time":281999,"text":"so Bujold --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283341,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284873,"text":"Say hello to Bujold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":289606,"text":"Bujold was used extensively\nat the World Trade Center"},{"time":292999,"text":"to go through Towers 1, 2 and 4."},{"time":295403,"text":"You're climbing into the rubble,\nrappelling down, going deep in spaces."},{"time":300072,"text":"And just to see the World Trade Center\nfrom Bujold's viewpoint, look at this."},{"time":304655,"text":"You're talking about a disaster\nwhere you can't fit a person or a dog --"},{"time":309748,"text":"and it's on fire."},{"time":311914,"text":"The only hope of getting\nto a survivor way in the basement,"},{"time":315672,"text":"you have to go through things\nthat are on fire."},{"time":317891,"text":"It was so hot, on one of the robots,\nthe tracks began to melt and come off."},{"time":323161,"text":"Robots don't replace people or dogs,"},{"time":325973,"text":"or hummingbirds or hawks or dolphins."},{"time":328518,"text":"They do things new."},{"time":330578,"text":"They assist the responders,\nthe experts, in new and innovative ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336291,"text":"The biggest problem is not\nmaking the robots smaller, though."},{"time":340744,"text":"It's not making them more heat-resistant."},{"time":342999,"text":"It's not making more sensors."},{"time":344780,"text":"The biggest problem is the data,\nthe informatics,"},{"time":348414,"text":"because these people need to get\nthe right data at the right time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352474,"text":"So wouldn't it be great if we could have\nexperts immediately access the robots"},{"time":357999,"text":"without having to waste any time\nof driving to the site,"},{"time":360999,"text":"so whoever's there,\nuse their robots over the Internet."},{"time":363956,"text":"Well, let's think about that."},{"time":365362,"text":"Let's think about a chemical\ntrain derailment in a rural county."},{"time":368758,"text":"What are the odds that the experts,\nyour chemical engineer,"},{"time":372624,"text":"your railroad transportation engineers,"},{"time":374510,"text":"have been trained on whatever UAV\nthat particular county happens to have?"},{"time":379395,"text":"Probably, like, none."},{"time":380952,"text":"So we're using these kinds of interfaces"},{"time":383366,"text":"to allow people to use the robots\nwithout knowing what robot they're using,"},{"time":387730,"text":"or even if they're using a robot or not."},{"time":392252,"text":"What the robots give you,\nwhat they give the experts, is data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398310,"text":"The problem becomes:\nwho gets what data when?"},{"time":401914,"text":"One thing to do is to ship\nall the information to everybody"},{"time":405831,"text":"and let them sort it out."},{"time":407367,"text":"Well, the problem with that\nis it overwhelms the networks,"},{"time":411247,"text":"and worse yet, it overwhelms\nthe cognitive abilities"},{"time":414957,"text":"of each of the people trying to get\nthat one nugget of information"},{"time":419490,"text":"they need to make the decision\nthat's going to make the difference."},{"time":423999,"text":"So we need to think\nabout those kinds of challenges."},{"time":427117,"text":"So it's the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428406,"text":"Going back to the World Trade Center,"},{"time":430666,"text":"we tried to solve that problem\nby just recording the data from Bujold"},{"time":434999,"text":"only when she was deep in the rubble,"},{"time":436999,"text":"because that's what the USAR team\nsaid they wanted."},{"time":440523,"text":"What we didn't know at the time"},{"time":443135,"text":"was that the civil engineers\nwould have loved,"},{"time":445757,"text":"needed the data as we recorded\nthe box beams, the serial numbers,"},{"time":449999,"text":"the locations, as we went into the rubble."},{"time":453343,"text":"We lost valuable data."},{"time":454834,"text":"So the challenge is getting all the data"},{"time":457237,"text":"and getting it to the right people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459441,"text":"Now, here's another reason."},{"time":461542,"text":"We've learned that some buildings --"},{"time":463877,"text":"things like schools,\nhospitals, city halls --"},{"time":467173,"text":"get inspected four times\nby different agencies"},{"time":471216,"text":"throughout the response phases."},{"time":474156,"text":"Now, we're looking, if we can get\nthe data from the robots to share,"},{"time":477449,"text":"not only can we do things like\ncompress that sequence of phases"},{"time":482323,"text":"to shorten the response time,"},{"time":484000,"text":"but now we can begin\nto do the response in parallel."},{"time":488382,"text":"Everybody can see the data."},{"time":489785,"text":"We can shorten it that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491999,"text":"So really, \"disaster robotics\"\nis a misnomer."},{"time":496227,"text":"It's not about the robots."},{"time":498146,"text":"It's about the data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500433,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503787,"text":"So my challenge to you:"},{"time":505768,"text":"the next time you hear about a disaster,"},{"time":508092,"text":"look for the robots."},{"time":509441,"text":"They may be underground,\nthey may be underwater,"},{"time":512590,"text":"they may be in the sky,"},{"time":514308,"text":"but they should be there."},{"time":516297,"text":"Look for the robots,"},{"time":517488,"text":"because robots are coming to the rescue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520259,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}